a new york artist was named as the winner of a 
nationwide contest to create a new image of the madonna for 
chicagos oldest roman catholic church 
bryan hunts entry a pair of oil pastel and graphite panels 
titled madonna and child i and ii was selected as the best of 
more than 400 entries sent by the nations artists to old st 
patricks church 
the rev jack wall pastor of old st patricks announced 
friday that hunts work was chosen from a field of 17 finalists by 
a jury of art critics and curators including a representative of 
the church 
we are very pleased with the jurors selection wall said 
we were seeking a dramatic way to relook at mary in the catholic 
church and we have found it in this winning piece 
as winner hunt will receive a purchase price of 10000 for the 
two panels which each measure 22 by 33 inches 
