neither michael dukakis nor his friend and 
moneyraiser bob farmer assumed great success when they sat down at 
the massachusetts governors breakfast table one day in the fall of 
1986 
dukakis was casting an eye toward the presidency and he had one 
question 
he said look if i decide to go for this thing will the 
money be there to wage a credible campaign farmer recalled 
farmer responded with some optimism but a day later he had 
second thoughts he called dukakis 
im troubled by one thing he told dukakis ive never 
raised money for a guy whos at 1 percent in the polls 
as it turned out farmer underestimated 
dukakis has been underestimated all along in this presidential 
campaign much as his fall opponent republican george bush has 
been 
critics fault dukakis for a cold aloofness a lack of passion 
and a presence that creates barely a ripple outside a staged event 
not until pennsylvanias primary tuesday where he won by 2to1 
