jacksons trips abroad and his work at chicagobased push people 
united to serve humanity brookins said 
says jackson their congregations are supportive of our 
efforts so if we need 8000 or 18000 we just indicate what we 
need 
the rev jim holley for instance said he has helped jackson 
finance his foreign diplomacy 
there are certain ministers that jesse can call and ask for 
1000 and well give it to him without any questions asked said 
holley pastor of little rock baptist church in detroit we have 
a network i remember when push couldnt make its payroll one time 
i had three hours to raise 8000 and i did it because of the 
cause 
to illustrate his point holley said that in 1984 the rev 
jasper williams of salem baptist church in atlanta regularly 
donated money to help support jacksons family while the candidate 
was campaigning and not drawing a salary 
when a trip abroad was planned holley said a telephone 
conference call was set up with jackson and several ministers 
all of us would say how much we can raise and ask him things 
like are you sure thats enough who do you want to take along 
with you holley said 
jackson also has accepted the hospitality of foreign governments 
to defray the costs of his hotel accomodations food and incountry 
travel during some of his trips abroad 
in august 1986 for instance as world attention focused on 
rioting in south africa jackson toured nigeria angola botswana 
tanzania mozambique zambia and zimbabwe and met with their 
leaders 
nigerian president ibrahim babangida provided an airplane 
jackson said his hotel accomodations food and other expenses were 
