am said robert finn spokesman for the california institute of 
technology in pasadena 
its epicenter was placed four miles southeast of pasadena on the 
fault that produced the october quake which caused millions of 
dollars in damage 
a quake measuring 30 on the richter scale hit just before 9 
am about 12 miles southeast of downtown san diego finn said 
no injuries or damage were reported in either quake sheriffs 
deputies said 
quakes with a richter reading of less than 35 can cause slight 
damage in a local area 
the richter scale is a measure of ground motion as recorded on 
seismographs every increase of one number means a tenfold increase 
in magnitude thus a reading of 75 reflects an earthquake 10 times 
stronger than one of 65 
