with the soviet academy of sciences 
following the explosion of 10 tons of tnt buried beneath the 
desert 100 miles north of reno and another 10ton shot 50 miles 
south of the nevada test site on friday a 15ton detonation was 
set off saturday about 100 miles east of carson city and 210 miles 
northeast of deep springs 
the blasts were monitored by soviet and american equipment here 
in the sierra nevada about midway between reno and las vegas and at 
two permanent defense council installations closer to the nevada 
test site 110 miles north of las vegas where all us underground 
nuclear detonations are conducted an additional 140 temporary 
monitoring stations were set up across nevada 
