site in kazakhstan 
because of the geology of the soviet union the readings there 
were much more pronounced than those so far in the fractured 
foundations of nevada 
it was a very small signal but it was a discernible signal 
ms eissler said of fridays first test she noted that a limited 
nuclear test ban treaty passed thursday by the house forbids 
detonations larger than one kiloton 100 times the strength of the 
10ton tnt blast 
she said fridays first test was recorded here at about three 
times normal background noise and the second explosion was barely 
detectable 
saturdays larger explosion registered about 10 times background 
noise ms eissler said 
the scientists initially thought fridays first detonation 
failed to register on any of the seismic monitors but a more 
detailed study indicated the test was recorded successfully 100 
seconds after the blast 
this is about the size wed expect in this terrain 
archambeau said he called nevadas complex geology a worstcase 
situation that will help us design networks that can do 
verification in these rather difficult areas 
the experiments are expected to show that any chances for 
cheating are about excluded under a test ban said evgeni 
