<TEXT>
a new drug for psoriasis is closely related to 
the acne drug accutane and is probably even more likely to produce 
birth defects when taken by pregnant women according to a 
published report 
the new york times reported in its sunday editions that at least 
seven babies have been born with defects to women who had taken the 
drug tegison though no cases have been been recorded in the united 
states 
the drug was licensed in the united states in december 1986 and 
is used to treat severe cases of psoriasis whose symptoms include 
scaly reddish patches of skin 
the newspaper said experts have called for restrictions on the 
distribution of tegison like those suggested for accutane last week 
by the food and drug administration 
tegison whose generic name is etretinate can remain dormant in 
bodily tissues at least two years after it is taken and can cause 
birth defects long after a woman stops taking it dr franz rosa of 
the food and drug administration told the times 
tegison is produced in the united states by roche laboratories 
of nutley nj a subsidiary of f hoffmanla rouche ltd of 
switzerland roche also makes accutane 
i think etretinate will be a much bigger problem than 
accutane said dr devendra kochhar of the jefferson medical 
college in philadelphia the number of women exposed will be 
less but etretinate is manyfold more toxic than accutane 
tegison carries a pregnancy warning saying that it has not yet 
been determined how long a woman must avoid pregnancy after taking 
the drug 
a spokeswoman for hoffmanla roche carolyn glynn told the 
times that the company was investigating 10 new related compounds 
for skin treatments so far pregnancy risk does seem to come 
with this class of drugs she said 
she said the company was considering whether to make the 
pregnancy warning more prominent on the package 
everything we do for accutane is certainly applicable to 
tegison she said last week the fda endorsed suggestions by the 
company that it strengthen its warning on accutane and make it 
harder for women to obtain 
tegison and accutane can cause facial deformities mental 
retardation and often lethal heart defects in babies born to users 
of the drug the newspaper said 
